article.linkText: Thomas scores 22, San Francisco defeats Fresno State 77-57
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- — Malik Thomas' 22 points helped San Francisco defeat Fresno State 77-57 on Friday night. Thomas was 8 of 12 shooting (4 for 6 from 3-point range) for the Dons (10-4). Marcus Williams scored 11 points, going 4 of 12 (3 for 9 from 3-point range). Mike Sharavjamts shot 4 for 7, including 2 for 4 from beyond the arc to finish with 10 points. Xavier Dusell led the Bulldogs (6-6) in scoring, finishing with nine points. Fresno State also got eight points from Leo Colimerio. In addition, Isaiah Pope had eight points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
